        public String getContentUrl()
        Description copied from interface: Document
        Returns the content URL of the document if the binding supports content URLs. Depending on the repository and the binding, the server might not return the content but an error message. Authentication data is not attached. That is, a user may have to re-authenticate to get the content.
        Specified by:

        Returns:
        the content URL of the document or null if the binding does not support content URLs

      • setContentStream

        public Document setContentStream(ContentStream contentStream,
                        boolean overwrite)
        Description copied from interface: Document
        Sets a new content stream for the document and refreshes this object afterwards. If the repository created a new version, this new document is returned. Otherwise the current document is returned.

        The stream in contentStream is consumed but not closed by this method.

        Specified by:
        setContentStream in interface Document
        Parameters:
        contentStream - the content stream
        overwrite - if this parameter is set to false and the document already has content, the repository throws a CmisContentAlreadyExistsException
        Returns:
        the updated document, or null if the repository did not return an object ID
        See Also:
        ObjectFactory.createContentStream(String, long, String, java.io.InputStream)

      • setContentStream

        public ObjectId setContentStream(ContentStream contentStream,
                        boolean overwrite,
                        boolean refresh)
        Description copied from interface: Document
        Sets a new content stream for the document. If the repository created a new version, the object ID of this new version is returned. Otherwise the object ID of the current document is returned.

        The stream in contentStream is consumed but not closed by this method.

        Specified by:
        setContentStream in interface Document
        Parameters:
        contentStream - the content stream
        overwrite - if this parameter is set to false and the document already has content, the repository throws a CmisContentAlreadyExistsException
        refresh - if this parameter is set to true, this object will be refreshed after the new content has been set
        Returns:
        the updated object ID, or null if the repository did not return an object ID
        See Also:
        ObjectFactory.createContentStream(String, long, String, java.io.InputStream)

      • appendContentStream

        public Document appendContentStream(ContentStream contentStream,
                           boolean isLastChunk)
        Description copied from interface: Document
        Appends a content stream to the content stream of the document and refreshes this object afterwards. If the repository created a new version, this new document is returned. Otherwise the current document is returned.

        The stream in contentStream is consumed but not closed by this method.

        Specified by:
        appendContentStream in interface Document
        Parameters:
        contentStream - the content stream
        isLastChunk - indicates if this stream is the last chunk of the content
        Returns:
        the updated document, or null if the repository did not return an object ID
        See Also:
        ObjectFactory.createContentStream(String, long, String, java.io.InputStream)

      • appendContentStream

        public ObjectId appendContentStream(ContentStream contentStream,
                           boolean isLastChunk,

        Description copied from interface: Document
        Appends a content stream to the content stream of the document. If the repository created a new version, the object ID of this new version is returned. Otherwise the object ID of the current document is returned.

        Specified by:
        appendContentStream in interface Document
